[Patient] Yo doc, I been tryna eat better to help with my heart failure. What kinda foods should I be eatin'? 
[Healthcare Specialist] Hey there! It's great that you're looking to make some changes. You should focus on eating more fruits and veggies, whole grains, and lean proteins like chicken or fish. 
[Patient] I hear you, doc. But what about all them fried foods I love so much? Can I still have those sometimes? 
[Healthcare Specialist] I understand where you're coming from, but fried foods can be high in unhealthy fats and sodium, which can worsen your heart failure. It's best to limit them as much as possible. 
[Patient] Got it, doc. What about snacks? I love me some chips and cookies. 
[Healthcare Specialist] Instead of chips and cookies, try snacking on nuts, seeds, or fresh fruit. They're healthier options that can still satisfy your cravings. 
[Patient] I see what you're sayin', doc. What about drinks? Can I still have my sweet tea? 
[Healthcare Specialist] Sweet tea can be high in sugar, which can be harmful for your heart. It's best to limit sugary drinks and opt for water, herbal tea, or unsweetened beverages instead. 
[Patient] Alright, doc. I'll try to make some changes to my diet. Any other tips for me? 
[Healthcare Specialist] Along with eating healthy, it's important to stay active and take your medications as prescribed. And don't forget to check in with me regularly so we can monitor your progress together. 
[Patient] Thanks for the advice, doc. I appreciate you lookin' out for me. 
[Healthcare Specialist] Of course! I'm here to help you every step of the way. Just remember, small changes can make a big difference in managing your heart failure.